#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "Domain Clustered Mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Domain mode is a way to centrally manage and publish the configuration for your servers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running a cluster in standard mode can quickly become aggravating as the cluster grows in size.  Every time you need\n"
"to make a configuration change, you have perform it on each node in the cluster.  Domain mode solves this problem by providing\n"
"a central place to store and publish configuration.  It can be quite complex to set up, but it is worth it in the end.\n"
"This capability is built into the {appserver_name} Application Server which {project_name} derives from.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "The guide will go over the very basics of domain mode.  Detailed steps on how to set up domain mode in a cluster should be obtained from the\n"
"       link:{appserver_admindoc_link}[_{appserver_admindoc_name}_].\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "Here are some of the basic concepts of running in domain mode.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "domain controller"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "The domain controller is a process that is responsible for storing, managing, and publishing the general configuration\n"
"for each node in the cluster.  This process is the central point from which nodes in a cluster obtain their configuration.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "host controller"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "The host controller is responsible for managing server instances on a specific machine.  You configure it to run\n"
"one or more server instances.  The domain controller can also interact with the host controllers on each machine to\n"
"manage the cluster.  To reduce the number of running process, a domain controller also acts as a host controller on\n"
"the machine it runs on.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "domain profile"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "A domain profile is a named set of configuration that can be used by a server to boot from.  A domain controller\n"
"can define multiple domain profiles that are consumed by different servers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:31
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:106
#, no-wrap
msgid "server group"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "A server group is a collection of servers.  They are managed and configured as one.  You can assign a domain profile to a server group and every service in that\n"
"group will use that domain profile as their configuration.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "In domain mode, a domain controller is started on a master node.  The configuration for the cluster resides in the domain controller.\n"
"Next a host controller is started on each machine in the cluster.  Each host controller deployment configuration specifies how\n"
"many {project_name} server instances will be started on that machine.  When the host controller boots up, it starts\n"
"as many {project_name} server instances as it was configured to do.  These server instances pull their configuration\n"
"from the domain controller.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "Domain Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "Various other chapters in this guide walk you through configuring various aspects like databases,\n"
"HTTP network connections, caches, and other infrastructure related things.  While standalone mode uses the _standalone.xml_ file to configure these things,\n"
"domain mode uses the _.../domain/configuration/domain.xml_ configuration file.  This is\n"
"where the domain profile and server group for the {project_name} server are defined.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "domain.xml"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:51
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/domain-file.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "Any changes you make to this file while the domain controller is running will not take effect and may even be overwritten\n"
"      by the server.  Instead use the the command line scripting or the web console of {appserver_name}.  See\n"
"      the link:{appserver_admindoc_link}[_{appserver_admindoc_name}_] for more information.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:58
#, no-wrap
msgid "Let's look at some aspects of this _domain.xml_ file.  The `auth-server-standalone` and `auth-server-clustered` `profile` XML blocks are where you are going to make the bulk of your configuration decisions.\n"
"You'll be configuring things here like network connections, caches, and database connections.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "auth-server profile"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:70
#, no-wrap
msgid "    <profiles>\n"
"        <profile name=\"auth-server-standalone\">\n"
"            ...\n"
"         </profile>\n"
"       <profile name=\"auth-server-clustered\">\n"
"           ...\n"
"        </profile>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:73
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `auth-server-standalone` profile is a non-clustered setup.  The `auth-server-clustered` profile is the clustered setup.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:75
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you scroll down further, you'll see various `socket-binding-groups` defined.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:76
#, no-wrap
msgid "socket-binding-groups"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:91
#, no-wrap
msgid "    <socket-binding-groups>\n"
"        <socket-binding-group name=\"standard-sockets\" default-interface=\"public\">\n"
"           ...\n"
"        </socket-binding-group>\n"
"        <socket-binding-group name=\"ha-sockets\" default-interface=\"public\">\n"
"           ...\n"
"        </socket-binding-group>\n"
"        <!-- load-balancer-sockets should be removed in production systems and replaced with a better softare or hardare based one -->\n"
"        <socket-binding-group name=\"load-balancer-sockets\" default-interface=\"public\">\n"
"           ...\n"
"        </socket-binding-group>\n"
"    </socket-binding-groups>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:97
#, no-wrap
msgid "This config defines the default port mappings for various connectors that are opened with each\n"
"{project_name} server instance.  Any value that contains `${...}` is a value that can be overriden on the command line\n"
"with the `-D` switch, i.e.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:100
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ domain.sh -Djboss.http.port=80\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:105
#, no-wrap
msgid "The definition of the server group for {project_name} resides in the `server-groups` XML block.  It specifies the domain profile\n"
"that is used (`default`) and also some default boot arguments for the Java VM when the host controller boots an instance.  It also\n"
"binds a `socket-binding-group` to the server group.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:124
#, no-wrap
msgid "    <server-groups>\n"
"        <!-- load-balancer-group should be removed in production systems and replaced with a better softare or hardare based one -->\n"
"        <server-group name=\"load-balancer-group\" profile=\"load-balancer\">\n"
"            <jvm name=\"default\">\n"
"                <heap size=\"64m\" max-size=\"512m\"/>\n"
"            </jvm>\n"
"            <socket-binding-group ref=\"load-balancer-sockets\"/>\n"
"        </server-group>\n"
"        <server-group name=\"auth-server-group\" profile=\"auth-server-clustered\">\n"
"            <jvm name=\"default\">\n"
"                <heap size=\"64m\" max-size=\"512m\"/>\n"
"            </jvm>\n"
"            <socket-binding-group ref=\"ha-sockets\"/>\n"
"        </server-group>\n"
"    </server-groups>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:128
#, no-wrap
msgid "Host Controller Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:134
#, no-wrap
msgid "{project_name} comes with two host controller configuration files that reside in the _.../domain/configuration/_ directory:\n"
"_host-master.xml_ and _host-slave.xml_.  _host-master.xml_ is configured to boot up a domain controller, a load balancer, and\n"
"one {project_name} server instance.  _host-slave.xml_ is configured to talk to the domain controller and boot up\n"
"one {project_name} server instance.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:138
#, no-wrap
msgid "The load balancer is not a required service.  It exists so that you can easily test drive clustering on your development\n"
"       machine.  While usable in production, you have the option of replacing it if you have a different hardware or software\n"
"       based load balancer you want to use.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:139
#, no-wrap
msgid "Host Controller Config"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:141
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/host-files.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:143
#, no-wrap
msgid "To disable the load balancer server instance, edit _host-master.xml_ and comment out or remove the `\"load-balancer\"` entry.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:151
#, no-wrap
msgid "    <servers>\n"
"        <!-- remove or comment out next line -->\n"
"        <server name=\"load-balancer\" group=\"loadbalancer-group\"/>\n"
"        ...\n"
"    </servers>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:157
#, no-wrap
msgid "Another interesting thing to note about this file is the declaration of the authentication server instance.  It has\n"
"a `port-offset` setting.  Any network port defined in the _domain.xml_ `socket-binding-group` or the server group\n"
"will have the value of `port-offset` added to it.  For this example domain setup we do this so that ports opened by\n"
"the load balancer server don't conflict with the authentication server instance that is started.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:166
#, no-wrap
msgid "    <servers>\n"
"        ...\n"
"        <server name=\"server-one\" group=\"auth-server-group\" auto-start=\"true\">\n"
"             <socket-bindings port-offset=\"150\"/>\n"
"        </server>\n"
"    </servers>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:168
#, no-wrap
msgid "Server Instance Working Directories"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:173
#, no-wrap
msgid "Each {project_name} server instance defined in your host files creates a working directory under _.../domain/servers/{SERVER NAME}_.\n"
"Additional configuration can be put there, and any temporary, log, or data files the server instance needs or creates go there too.\n"
"The structure of these per server directories ends up looking like any other {appserver_name} booted server.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:174
#, no-wrap
msgid "Working Directories"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_installation/topics/operating-mode/domain.adoc:176
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/domain-server-dir.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

